{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.16",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 16 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:2",
      "text": "“I have heard many such things; miserable comforters are you all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:3",
      "text": "Shall windy words have an end? Or what provokes you that you answer?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:4",
      "text": "I also could speak as you do, if you were in my place; I could join words together against you, and shake my head at you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:5",
      "text": "I could strengthen you with my mouth, and the solace of my lips would assuage your pain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:6",
      "text": "“If I speak, my pain is not assuaged, and if I forbear, how much of it leaves me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:7",
      "text": "Surely now God has worn me out; he has made desolate all my company.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:8",
      "text": "And he has shriveled me up, which is a witness against me; and my leanness has risen up against me, it testifies to my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:9",
      "text": "He has torn me in his wrath, and hated me; he has gnashed his teeth at me; my adversary sharpens his eyes against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:10",
      "text": "Men have gaped at me with their mouth, they have struck me insolently upon the cheek, they mass themselves together against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:11",
      "text": "God gives me up to the ungodly, and casts me into the hands of the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:12",
      "text": "I was at ease, and he broke me asunder; he seized me by the neck and dashed me to pieces; he set me up as his target,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:13",
      "text": "his archers surround me. He slashes open my kidneys, and does not spare; he pours out my gall on the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:14",
      "text": "He breaks me with breach upon breach; he runs upon me like a warrior.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:15",
      "text": "I have sewed sackcloth upon my skin, and have laid my strength in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:16",
      "text": "My face is red with weeping, and on my eyelids is deep darkness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:17",
      "text": "although there is no violence in my hands, and my prayer is pure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:18",
      "text": "“O earth, cover not my blood, and let my cry find no resting place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:19",
      "text": "Even now, behold, my witness is in heaven, and he that vouches for me is on high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:20",
      "text": "My friends scorn me; my eye pours out tears to God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:21",
      "text": "that he would maintain the right of a man with God, like that of a man with his neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.16.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:22",
      "text": "For when a few years have come I shall go the way whence I shall not return.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
